songs.title: Voodoo (Demo)
songs.lyrics:
[Intro]
I-It's your voo...
I-It's your voo...

[Verse 1]
I can't get away
Found a home in your heartbeat
I keep coming back again
There's a madness that surrounds me
And when you're a thousand miles away
I'm holding on for you
I get on my knees to pray
'Cause I've fallen under you

[Chorus]
It's your voodoo
It's your voodoo
(I-It's your voo...)
Is this what they call love?
'Cause I can't get enough
Must be voodoo
(I-It's your voo...)

[Verse 2]
You're my heavy rain
You drench me off of nothing
For all you gotta say, at least can you mean something?
And when you're a thousand miles away, what am I supposed to do?
It's strange, 'cause your love stayed
I've fallen under you

[Chorus]
It's your voodoo
(It's your) It's your voodoo
(I-It's your voo...)
Is this what they call love?
'Cause I can't get enough
Must be voodoo
(I-It's your voo...)

[Interlude]
(I-It's your voo...)
Voodoo, voodoo
Voodoo, voodoo
(I-It's your voo...)
Voodoo, voodoo
Voodoo, voodoo

[Bridge]
Why won't you let me go?
I'm under your control
Fighting to let you go
And I can't get out
Why won't you let me go?
I'm under your control
Fighting to let you go
And I can't get out

[Chorus]
It's your voodoo (voodoo, voodoo)
(It's your) It's your voodoo (voodoo, voodoo)
(I-It's your voo...)
Is this what they call love? (voodoo, voodoo)
'Cause I can't get enough
Must be voodoo (voodoo, voodoo)
(I-It's your voo...)

[Bridge]
(Voodoo, voodoo)
It's your voo...
(Voodoo, voodoo)
Is this what they call love?
(Voodoo, voodoo)
Must be voodoo
(Voodoo, voodoo)
